Ok... so here are some random college updates:

* Field Hockey looks like it's gonna be good  (Hell, Farmer isn't my coach anymore!!!)
* The boys are ok... nothing special haha! jk! There are tons of hotties, but a lot of jackasses too :/
* Classes are better now that I fixed my schedule... I am out by at least 2 every day :)
* I think I was placed in the wrong dorm, I want to live with Sammy ;)
* Last nite some really weird kids streaked in front of Riley... and for the most part were sober!  WHAT IS THAT?!?!

Oh well! College rocks! Can't believe I had to wait 18 years for this! 

I miss all my Keene people, but rest easy knowing you all are having a wonderful time at school too!!  (Not missing KHS however)

I essentially did nothing all day, and then tonite I went Galactic Bowling with Julie, Alli, my friend Dave from WPI, and Dave's friend Tom.  It was a blast!  It was awesome to see Dave again, and Tom was a blast as well.  (And surprisingly the name didn't do anything to me!! There is a God after all!)

But all-in-all I had an AWESOME night and can't wait to hang out with some of these people again!! ;)

OOOK... Here's a run down of everything I have done in the last week! Saturday the 17th was Bay States. That was awesome! I got to play a lot of field hockey and hang out with the coolest team ever (sorry, but KHS doesn't compare). After playing we went to Whit's house and swam and ate, which also rocked! haha. Sunday I worked... b/c that's what I do, I am officially Hannaford's bitch :( Monday through Thursday I worked and drove to WPI every afternoon to coach at camp. All I can say is that those were four of the greatest days of the entire summer. There were a lot of really cute girls who were so eager to learn about field hockey and it was adorable! Plus, I got to hang out with JRoy (the weeble), Whit (who will shoot you with her field hockey stick if she gets angry), Lynn (is crazy... like me), Nowill and Jenelle (who are fun to horse around with). Friday I worked and then drove down to CT to hang out with Tom and go to a party his grandparents were having on Saturday. All was going well till I got onto I-91 and my car started saying it was over-heating! So I called Mom and Dad to see what I should do and they told me to start heading home so I could trade cars and take the good ol' minivan. Finally after driving back to Chesterfield hill, I got the new car and headed off to CT again. Saturday was the party and all I can say is his family is a lot of fun! His uncle Patrick brought a potato cannon to the party and they were shooting potato's all over the place (which thankfully I brought my camera to record some footage of). We got back to his house around 11 and around 11:45 I proceeded to drive home. AND to add to all this, my cell battery was completely dead, so I got about 20 minutes out of South Windsor, realized my cell was dead, and pulled into a gas station to use a pay-phone to call my parents. When I finally get through to them I realized that they have called my friends trying to find out if they have heard from me, thinking I was dead. So now all my friends think I am dead, my parents WERE thinking I was dead, and there was much chaos on my behalf. OOPS!!! Then around 1:15 I reached Keene, drove to Alli's where I had been planning on sleeping over, where I was greeted by Em almost killing me for making her think I was dead. I finally got home, plugged in the cell and found I had NINE VOICEMAILS and one text message, all of which were people wondering where I was. Did I mention OOPS!!!? Now it's Sunday, I've grocery shopped and have NO intention of driving anywhere more than 20 minutes MAX from my house. I am SICK of driving (regardless of the fact that I did it voluntarily all week...)

Leo - Your Love Profile

Your positive traits:

You're almost always the center of attention - and easy for potential dates to spot
Your happiness and optimism is appealing to all... and contagious!
You don't hold grudges - getting over little fights is no problem for you

Your negative traits:

You tend to ignore relationship problems, until they are too big to handle
You crave luxury, and you are disappointed with partners who can't provide you with it
If someone does you wrong, you'll coldly and cruely break their heart

Your ideal partner:

Someone high status enough to bring you more attention - but not so great that they upstage you
Makes you laugh and brings excitement to everything you do together
Is aggressive and confident enough to butt heads with you every so often

Your dating style:

High expectations. You need to be impressed with an incredible first date for a second one to occur.

Your seduction style:

You like to make the first move - you're fearless about initiating things
Passionate. You really get into any intimate act.
Aggressive. Most of the time, you find yourself wanting sex more than your partner.

Tips for the future:

Try to not need so much attention. You'll feel less ignored, guaranteed.
Learn to love your parnter for who they are - not how they help advance your life.
Let your partner shine occasionally. You don't always have to be the alpha dog.

Best color to attract mate: Gold

Best day for a date: Sunday

ME! haha! I really haven't updated in forever and I am sorry if it offended all 4 of you who actually try to read this on a regular basis! The most important things that have happened since I last updated: Got to help out "coaching" at a field hockey camp at WPI. Went to Rhode Island and in the process saw Ryan Graves, Alethia G., and Caitlin Dowley. I got my ears peirced... second holes and the cartilage of my left ear. On the 4th of July Em Harris, who happened to be in RI at the time, stopped by in Bristol at my grandmother's house and stayed the night. We then got to go out and guard the chairs* on the parade route with my dad and cousin John at 5:30 AM. On the plus side I got to drive John's new Accura to Sip and Dip to get donuts! * You all have to understand this one thing about the 4th in Bristol... they take this holiday VERY serious! They have the oldest parade in the country. The parade route, instead of having yellow lines painted down the middle of the road, YEAR-ROUND they have red, white, and blue stripes. The deal with the hardcore parade lovers is that you can legally go out and set up chairs along the parade route at 2AM for a parade that doesn't start until 10:30AM. THIS is how important this one parade is... it also doesn't help that my grandmother is OBSESSED with the 4th... she waits all year for it and gets all geared up starting late June, singing random patriotic songs and wearing red, white, and blue. (Good thing she is by far the greatest grandmother ever!!) I wish I was pulling all your legs about this whole deal, but I'm not. p.s. I miss all the people who have recently left me! Jules and Alli in England... Julie O @ camp in NY... Kol in the Cape (though I think she is returning soon)... J2 in New Jersey with her horsies... TOM in St. Thomas (coming home tomorrow!!! :D)... and I am sure there are more people who are gone, but didn't feel the need to tell me they left, so I don't miss them too much hehe!

All I can say is that I love and miss every single one of you already!!  I can't honestly believe that I will no longer be attending school with the same kids I have grown up with.  I mean sure, I'll still see some of you often, but other people I won't see for another 10 years!  I just don't think I can handle that... :(

It hasn't officially hit me that this is the way it is, and if anyone who has already graduated can tell me when it will... it would be much appreciated.

Project Grad was amazingly fun!  It was awesome to hang out with some of the most fun people I've ever known!  I hope we all get together this summer and do WILD and CRAZY things!

You all have touched my life in some special way at one point or another, I can't thank you enough for that!  You have made me who I am today!  You all mean the world to me, and it breaks my heart to have to say goodbye to any of you!  Never lose touch!
